        <ab xml:id="block_A" xml:lang="en" facs="https://momoiro.hallyu.io/mishkan/iiif/3/mishkan%2Fa3f6fae8-9ac8-4a8b-9632-93d6a9941699.jp2/854,400,3710,1501/max/0/default.jpg">
          The desert mishkan was a portable sanctuary. Its care was guarded by the Levites and<lb/>
        the priests yet it invited all to bring their offerings. Today, we are all caretakers of<lb/>
        Mishkan T&apos;filah; may our offerings be acceptable before God.<lb/>
        May all who enter find joy, solace and meaning.<lb/>
        RABBI ELYSE D. FRISHMAN<lb/>
        Editor<lb/>
        RABBI PETER S. KNOBEL<lb/>
        Chair of the Editorial Committee
        </ab>
